<TITLE> 4 children killed in Ctg fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Feb 13 (bdnews24.com)  Four brothers and sisters aged 10 and under were killed in a fire at a low-income housing colony in Chittagong city on Saturday, which may have started with a mosquito net catching alight, firemen said. The fire broke out at the thatched-roof home of Hosne Ara Begum at Mohammadpur Colony at around 3am, Mohammad Morshed, an officer at Agrabad Fire Service Control Room, told bdnews24.com. It spread to at least four adjacent residences in the workers' colony. The blaze was doused at around 4:30am, Morshed said. Hosne Ara's four children were burnt alive in the fire. They were Nurunnabi, 10, Salauddin, 7, Alauddin, 5, and Tanzina, 4. Two people were also injured and admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital bd
